OL,6,FMeanwhile in Scotland, the scheduling
OL,7,Fof the local soap River City has
OL,8,Fbecome a little erratic.  It was off
OL,9,Fair last summer and is now off the
OL,10,Fair again until May. For its first 18
OL,11,Fyears it never took a break.
OL,13,FWhy is this a problem?
OL,15,FFor a soap or a continuing drama,
OL,16,Fregularity is vital. The viewer needs
OL,17,Fto know it is there at a certain
OL,18,Ftime.  Otherwise the relationship
OL,19,Fgoes. When the relationship goes and
OL,20,Fthe ratings fall, a programme's
OL,21,Ffuture can inevitably fall into
OL,22,Fquestion.
